HEADWORD: Shuffler
<hw>Shuf"fler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
shuffles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Either one of the three common
American scaup ducks. See <xex>Scaup duck</xex>, under
<er>Scaup</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shufflewing</ent>⟦br⟧
